A dramatic high-quality photograph capturing an intense scene from the beaches of Normandy during the D-Day invasion. The image shows American soldiers in full combat gear running across a sandy beach under a rainy morning sky. Their faces are etched with determination and fear as they charge towards waiting tanks that have just arrived on shore.

The lens flare adds to the cinematic quality, reflecting off the bayonet-clad rifles of the soldiers and glinting off the sun-bleached metal of the landing craft. The sea is a turbulent mess behind them, with Allied ships bobbing in the waves as they bombard enemy positions offshore.

In the distance, you can make out other boats and small crafts ferrying additional troops and supplies ashore, while German gun emplacements dot the cliffs above, their muzzles trained on the advancing American forces. The photograph is shot in crisp black & white to heighten the drama of the moment, with each soldier's face clearly visible despite the rain.

The background is slightly out of focus, adding a layer of tension as the soldiers' lives hang in the balance on that fateful day in 1944. The image captures the chaos and bravery of the D-Day landing in vivid detail.

nodes.title: Pick Models.
widgets_values:
Pick Safetensors / GGUF Models, VAE, CLIP and Upscale model.
(see notes on the left for download links)

FP8 is recommended, GGUF Q4_K_S should work on 16GB VRAM
Use block swap 39 if you want to use biggest model for your GPU

nodes.title: Merge Loras ( disable for GGUF or if error)
KJ Sampler Advanced Settings
widgets_values:
Kijai's WanVideoWrapper has some interesting features.

- Blocks To Swap 
Choose how many memory blocks to move from GPU VRAM to CPU RAM. 
0 = All in GPU, 39 = Maximum offloading to RAM
Helpful if you run out of VRAM

- Model Base Precision
You can choose a precision here, but FP16_FAST seems to work just fine

- Model Quantization
If using FP8 on NVIDIA 4xxx cards, then use FP8_e4m3fn_scaled
Older cards may need to use FP_e5m2_scaled

- Accelarator
Default is SDPA, but if you have Sage Attention installed you can choose 'SAGEATTN"

- Model Offloading

Where the WAN Model needs to be stored. Choose offload_device unless you got a lot of VRAM.
( > 40 GB VRAM I Assume)

- Offloading Model After Sampling
I believe this keeps the model in main memory or something. You can change it and see what happens

- Text Encoder Offloading
To encode the prompt you can offload this to CPU if you do not have so much VRAM.

nodes.title: Warning (!)
widgets_values:
Please note that this an EXPERIMENTAL EXPERT workflow!

Since this workflow uses Kijai's Videowrapper, it comes with more advanced features (block swap) but requires more settings fiddeling.
Please use the other workflow (SAFE_GGUF) if you are a beginner or encounter errors.
Sometimes a restart of the workflow is needed after changing model related settings.

Note that for GGUF, disable the light lora, set Quantization to disabled and do not use scaled precision.

nodes.title: Pick Resolution & Steps
widgets_values:
Pick resolution using Resolution Master.

If needed, you can click the "Blue" and "Red" text in the top-right to set a custom width and height respectively.
 
At the bottom, choose the steps for first and total pass.
Default of 3 and 6 should work with light lora.
Otherwise use 30 steps without light lora.
Hint: For best (skin) realism use without light lora.

Note that 1920x1080, 1280x720, 720x1280 are Wan Resolutions.
Base model does not like 1440x1440 and 1080x1920 so much, but can be tried with trained loras.

Ideally, set to 1440x1440, 1920x1080 or 1080x1440.

nodes.title: Instructions
widgets_values:
A workflow for generating high quality images using either GGUF or Safetensors, with the option of using a lighting lora to speed up at the cost of realism. Upscaling and film grain options are provided.

Note:


0. Note that a Yellow Option menu on the leftis present to enable / disable some features.

1. Pick models on the left of the workflow.

2. Pick resolution on the lower left of this note.

3. Configure a Project Name (file prefix) below.

- Choose whether to use upscaling or not.
- Choose amount of images to generate
- Set a positive and negative prompt
- Enable film grain effect optionally for pseduo "realism".
- Enable Bleach Bypass effect optionally for movie effect.
Mutliple parameters are available. Consider setting the seed to fixed so you can experiment with different parameters.

- Choose whether to bypass the Light Lora (remove or set to 0 strength if you don't want to use it)

- Choose any Text2Video loras that you will use.
You can use both 2.1 loras and 2.2 low loras.
(Sometimes 2.1 loras need a bit more strength)

4. Choose aditional options on the right

Files are saved in the ComfyUI Output folder, in the following directory scheme:

JXL2\Projects\<Project Name>\<Project Name>_IMG_xxxxxx.png
